ritis atrofica","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"132","parent":"121","text":"Forma activa: metilcobalamina 1000 mcg/dia VO (preferir si neuropatia)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"133","parent":"121","text":"SEGUIMIENTO: control B12\\Nserico a los 3 meses post-inicio","guid":"Srm9yIg7rz2KblIuXlZZyQ","children":[{"id":"134","parent":"133","text":"Objetivo: >400 pg/mL","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"135","parent":"133","text":"Si persiste baja → evaluar causa (anticuerpos anti-FI, gastroscopia)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"136","parent":"133","text":"En AM con metformina: controlar B12 c/12 meses","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"137","parent":"120","text":"HIERRO /\\NFERRITINA","guid":"iTjRW7Cx94ZvJTkiGvlO5Q","children":[{"id":"138","parent":"137","text":"Ferritina objetivo en adulto mayor CON SBA: >30 ng/mL (algunos autores >50)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"139","parent":"137","text":"Ferritina <15 ng/mL → ferropenia absoluta","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"140","parent":"137","text":"Ferritina 15-30 ng/mL + sintomas → ferropenia funcional → tratar","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"141","parent":"137","text":"Hemoglobina objetivo: mujer >12 g/dL / hombre >13 g/dL","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"142","parent":"137","text":"Saturacion transferrina objetivo: >20%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"143","parent":"137","text":"Suplementacion oral:\\Nsulfato ferroso 200 mg\\N(65 mg Fe elemental)","guid":"vCMgssf--JYzfPbMhsL3mQ","children":[{"id":"144","parent":"143","text":"1-2 comprimidos/dia EN AYUNAS o c/12h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"145","parent":"143","text":"Con vitamina C 200 mg → mejora absorcion","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"146","parent":"143","text":"Dias alternos (evidencia 2021): igual eficacia, mejor tolerancia GI","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"147","parent":"143","text":"Duracion: 3-6 meses post-normalizacion ferritina","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"148","parent":"137","text":"Suplementacion IV: hierro sacarosa / carboximaltosa 